@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";
    var greetingParams = new Dictionary<string, string>
    {
        { "userName", "John" },
        { "itemCount", "5" }
    };
    var itemsParams = new Dictionary<string, string>
    {
        { "userName", "John" }
    };
}

<div class="text-center">
    <h1 class="display-4">
        <translaas group="common" entry="welcome" lang="@L.English" />
    </h1>
    <p>
        <translaas group="common" entry="welcome.message" lang="@L.English" />
    </p>
    <p class="text-muted">
        <small>All samples use the same Translaas project (<code>translaas-sdk-samples</code>) to demonstrate cross-platform translation sharing.</small>
    </p>
</div>

<div class="row mt-5">
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <h2>Translation Examples</h2>
        
        <div class="card mb-3">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h3>1. Tag Helper Usage</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>Using the <code>&lt;translaas&gt;</code> tag helper:</p>
                <pre><code>&lt;translaas group="common" entry="welcome" lang="@L.English" /&gt;</code></pre>
                <p>Result: <translaas group="common" entry="welcome" lang="@L.English" /></p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mb-3">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h3>2. Static Helper Usage</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>Using the <code>Translaas.T()</code> static helper:</p>
                <pre><code>@TranslaasMvc.T(Html, "common", "welcome", L.English)</code></pre>
                <p>Result: @TranslaasMvc.T(Html, "common", "welcome", L.English)</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mb-3">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h3>3. Direct Service Injection</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>Using injected <code>ITranslaasService</code> (already injected in _ViewImports.cshtml):</p>
                <pre><code>@await TranslaasService.T("common", "welcome", L.English)</code></pre>
                <p>Result: @await TranslaasService.T("common", "welcome", L.English)</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mb-3">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h3>4. Pluralization</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>Using pluralization with the <code>number</code> attribute:</p>
                <pre><code>&lt;translaas group="messages" entry="item" lang="@L.English" number="1" /&gt;
&lt;translaas group="messages" entry="item" lang="@L.English" number="5" /&gt;</code></pre>
                <p>1 item: <translaas group="messages" entry="item" lang="@L.English" number="1" /></p>
                <p>5 items: <translaas group="messages" entry="item" lang="@L.English" number="5" /></p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mb-3">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h3>5. Multiple Languages</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>Switching languages:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>English (@L.English): <translaas group="common" entry="welcome" lang="@L.English" /></li>
                    <li>French (@L.French): <translaas group="common" entry="welcome" lang="@L.French" /></li>
                    <li>Spanish (@L.Spanish): <translaas group="common" entry="welcome" lang="@L.Spanish" /></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mb-3">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h3>6. Named Parameters</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>Using named parameters with <code>ITranslaasService.T()</code>:</p>
                <pre><code>var parameters = new Dictionary&lt;string, string&gt;
{
    { "userName", "John" },
    { "itemCount", "5" }
};
await TranslaasService.T("messages", "greeting", L.English, parameters: parameters)</code></pre>
                <p>Translation with parameters: @await TranslaasService.T("messages", "greeting", L.English, parameters: greetingParams)</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mb-3">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h3>7. Combining Number and Named Parameters</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>Combining <code>number</code> and named parameters:</p>
                <pre><code>var parameters = new Dictionary&lt;string, string&gt;
{
    { "userName", "John" }
};
await TranslaasService.T("messages", "items", L.English, number: 5, parameters: parameters)</code></pre>
                <p>Translation with number and parameters: @await TranslaasService.T("messages", "items", L.English, number: 5, parameters: itemsParams)</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card mb-3">
            <div class="card-header">
                <h3>8. Automatic Language Resolution (NEW!)</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>With language providers configured, you can omit the <code>lang</code> parameter:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Tag Helper:</strong> <code>&lt;translaas group="common" entry="welcome" /&gt;</code></li>
                    <li><strong>Static Helper:</strong> <code>@Translaas.T(Html, "common", "welcome")</code></li>
                    <li><strong>Service:</strong> <code>await TranslaasService.T("common", "welcome")</code></li>
                </ul>
                <p>Language is resolved from (in order):</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>HTTP Request (route, query string, header, cookie)</li>
                    <li>Thread Culture (<code>CultureInfo.CurrentUICulture</code>)</li>
                    <li>Default Language (from <code>TranslaasOptions.DefaultLanguage</code>)</li>
                </ol>
                <p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>With explicit lang: <translaas group="common" entry="welcome" lang="@L.English" /></li>
                    <li>Automatic resolution: <translaas group="common" entry="welcome" /></li>
                </ul>
                <p><small class="text-muted">Try adding <code>?lang=fr</code> to the URL to see automatic language resolution!</small></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
